Project Rules

Before any code change: write a short plan (3–6 steps) and wait.

🚨 CRITICAL: Before creating/deleting packages, services, or major structural changes:
- Write the plan
- Wait for explicit user approval
- Do NOT proceed without confirmation

Read relevant repo files first (don't guess). If info is missing, ask one focused question or state one assumption and continue.

Work in small steps: implement one step, stop, summarize, then continue.

Keep diffs minimal and reversible; avoid "big rewrites".

Preserve existing APIs/contracts unless explicitly asked; if you must change them, call it out clearly and update consumers.

Follow repo conventions (TypeScript settings, folder structure, lint/format, naming).

Backend: for logic changes, include input validation + consistent error shape + at least one meaningful test.

Frontend: include loading/error/empty states + basic accessibility (labels, button types).

Avoid new dependencies unless clearly justified; propose the simplest option first.

Output format every time:

What you're going to do (plan or step)

Files to change

The change (diff/snippets)

How to test
